        <h2>How to Copy the Glyphs</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Focus the input box of the codepoint you want</li>
            <li>Select all (<kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>A</kbd> or <kbd>‚åò</kbd>+<kbd>A</kbd>)</li>
            <li>Copy (<kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>C</kbd> or <kbd>‚åò</kbd>+<kbd>C</kbd>)</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Using a Script to Enter Unicode</h2>
        <p>An easy method to enter special characters is by using an AutoHotkey script. You can use the Send command with codepoint literals like so:</p>
        <code>CapsLock &  \::Send {U+0300}</code>
        <p>The above allows you to use caps-lock+backslash as a hotkey to send a combining grave accent (attaches to the previous character). I use a series of hotkeys to more easily type accents and symbols, you can check that out at <a href="https://github.com/kmgb/character-input-ahk">this repository</a>.</p>

